00:00:03.460 --> 00:00:08.260
Grilled Bulgogi (UenYang Style Korean BBQ)

00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:15.880
Remove any excess moisture with paper towel from the meat.

00:00:20.280 --> 00:00:24.800
Chop onion and garlic finely.

00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:37.680
Remove the core of green onion and chop the bottoms and tops finely.

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:51.520
Add soy sauce, plum extract, pepper, cooking alcohol, syrup and sugar to a bowl and stir to combine.

00:00:57.680 --> 00:01:00.680
Add in the chopped garlic, onion and green onion.

00:01:10.840 --> 00:01:13.300
Flatten the meat with a knife by scoring it finely. (Be careful not to cut the meat all the way through)

00:01:23.420 --> 00:01:30.040
Marinate the meat and let it sit for about an hour.

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:37.000
Form the meat into flat disc shapes

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:53.240
Heat up a frying pan, add some oil and cook the meat until it's almost cooked (about 80%. If you're not gonna a grill afterwards, cook the meat all the way through)

00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:11.400
Heat up the grill a bit and brush over some oil.

00:02:17.180 --> 00:02:22.560
Put the meat onto the grill and cook it over low heat.

00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:32.520
Finish it off with some crushed pine nuts and you're done!

00:02:43.580 --> 00:02:45.100
Ingredients
450g of beef, some crushed pine nuts

00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:46.200
Sauce
4T of soy sauce, 1T of sugar and syrup each, 1T of minced garlic, 1/4 of one onion,

00:02:46.200 --> 00:02:47.340
1T of plum extract, 1/3 of green onion, 1/2t of pepper and 2T of cooking alcohol

